1
00:00:03,250 --> 00:00:07,370
Why aren't you eating? It's not to your liking?

2
00:00:07,370 --> 00:00:11,470
No, no, it's really good.
Episode 8

3
00:00:11,470 --> 00:00:15,540
It has just been a long time since I had such delicious food.

4
00:00:15,540 --> 00:00:19,900
Really? Let's eat out more often, just the two of us.

5
00:00:31,070 --> 00:00:34,830
- You were getting yelled at a lot back there.
- Pardon?

6
00:00:34,830 --> 00:00:40,360
When we were rehearsing. I heard everything, when Manager Yun was venting her anger on you.

7
00:00:40,360 --> 00:00:44,570
Don't take it to heart. She did it on purpose so I can see.

8
00:00:44,570 --> 00:00:49,270
- She wasn't mad at you.
- Yes.

9
00:00:49,980 --> 00:00:57,100
- That's that. But do you and him really help one another to sleep?
- Huh?

10
00:00:58,010 --> 00:01:00,540
Oh, Jang Yun...

11
00:01:01,270 --> 00:01:03,990
No, it's not that...

12
00:01:03,990 --> 00:01:09,130
It's just a part-time job. It's like a morning call, helping me sleep at night through a call.

13
00:01:09,130 --> 00:01:13,810
I have insomnia, so I need a bit of help.

14
00:01:13,810 --> 00:01:18,740
Insomnia? You said that you slept well earlier.

15
00:01:18,740 --> 00:01:23,920
That has been going on for a while right? Do you still struggle with it?

16
00:01:23,920 --> 00:01:25,470
It happens.

17
00:01:25,470 --> 00:01:30,120
- Then from now on, I need to learn how to help you fall asleep.
- What?

18
00:01:30,120 --> 00:01:34,910
Why are you so surprised? Eat everything on the plate, no leftovers.

19
00:01:34,910 --> 00:01:37,080
Yes...

20
00:01:43,810 --> 00:01:49,330
Yu Da: Welcome to the Jungle

21
00:01:50,380 --> 00:01:56,310
Today's Hot News: the Sinyeong Philharmonic couple is eating a full-course meal.

22
00:01:58,550 --> 00:02:02,090
Nam Ju Wan

23
00:02:03,550 --> 00:02:07,290
The number you have dialed is not available—

24
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:11,940
Now what is this?

25
00:02:24,150 --> 00:02:26,900
Do you work here?

26
00:02:28,010 --> 00:02:33,680
There are a lot of people coming here today.

27
00:02:35,550 --> 00:02:40,800
- How did you get hurt?
- I got hurt somehow.

28
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:46,800
This is fun. Aren't you going to ask why I'm waiting here? Are you not curious?

29
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:49,780
Do I have to be curious?

30
00:02:49,780 --> 00:02:56,410
No, you don't have to. We've met before, right?

31
00:02:56,410 --> 00:02:59,720
Before becoming fellow orchestra members.

32
00:02:59,720 --> 00:03:02,220
Hmm, I don't remember.

33
00:03:02,220 --> 00:03:08,510
Then why do I think that I've seen you before? Why do you seem so familiar?

34
00:03:08,510 --> 00:03:14,330
- That's none of my business.
- I've definitely seen you before.

35
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:19,000
Where have I seen you before?

36
00:03:19,970 --> 00:03:25,950
Take you concern off of me. I don't like people being interested in me.

37
00:03:33,550 --> 00:03:36,180
Where have I seen him before?

38
00:03:39,550 --> 00:03:45,180
Today's Hot News: the Sinyeong Philharmonic couple is eating a full-course meal.

39
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:04,090
Are you waiting for me?

40
00:04:13,810 --> 00:04:16,990
If you wanted to see me this much, you should've called.

41
00:04:16,990 --> 00:04:20,220
Who says I wanted to see you?

42
00:04:20,220 --> 00:04:23,130
When did you come here? I didn't see you coming.

43
00:04:23,130 --> 00:04:26,410
Just now. So, you were waiting for me.

44
00:04:26,410 --> 00:04:28,900
No, I wasn't.

45
00:04:31,420 --> 00:04:35,000
Are you allowed to drink when you're injured?

46
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:40,780
Non-alcoholic. It's not a serious wound and it doesn't even hurt anymore.

47
00:04:40,780 --> 00:04:46,620
Really? That's good. I was worried.

48
00:04:46,620 --> 00:04:53,310
- About me?
- Of course, because I'm interested in you.

49
00:04:57,320 --> 00:05:02,450
Did you, perhaps, see the bulletin board?

50
00:05:05,930 --> 00:05:11,780
I don't really care about the others but I don't want you to misunderstand.

51
00:05:11,780 --> 00:05:17,420
With the conductor, before, it was an actual welcome dinner.

52
00:05:17,420 --> 00:05:22,880
During today's rehearsal, I got in trouble with Manager Yun. So, because of that, he offered me dinner.

53
00:05:22,880 --> 00:05:28,840
As for the previous picture posted on the bulletin board, that was to help him pick a present.

54
00:05:28,840 --> 00:05:34,680
Although I don't know exactly who Yu Da is, how she took the picture or why she keeps spreading this rumor,

55
00:05:34,680 --> 00:05:41,570
the conductor and I are truly not in that kind of relationship.

56
00:05:43,860 --> 00:05:48,840
Please don't misunderstand.

57
00:06:02,990 --> 00:06:06,930
I'm just asking, just in case.

58
00:06:11,590 --> 00:06:16,570
- Do you think I like you?
- What?

59
00:06:16,570 --> 00:06:21,490
Being interested and liking someone is a bit different. Don't you think?

60
00:06:21,490 --> 00:06:26,530
What do you— What does it mean to be interested in someone without liking them?

61
00:06:26,530 --> 00:06:30,320
If you are interested, you can end up liking someone.

62
00:06:30,320 --> 00:06:36,750
What do you— Are you playing word games with me?

63
00:06:44,890 --> 00:06:52,070
It's the part-time fees I owe you. I don't want to hear you sing, so don't call me.

64
00:07:14,810 --> 00:07:18,260
Do you think I like you?

65
00:07:18,260 --> 00:07:23,710
Being interested and liking someone is a bit different. Don't you think?

66
00:07:24,460 --> 00:07:27,600
Since when did he make me so confused?

67
00:07:50,350 --> 00:07:53,940
This guy really has no manners.

68
00:07:56,590 --> 00:07:58,990
You're not sleeping.

69
00:07:58,990 --> 00:08:04,620
- What are you doing here, this late? I told you not to call.
- That's why I came here in person.

70
00:08:05,740 --> 00:08:09,750
- Can I come in and sing for you?
- What did you say?

71
00:08:09,750 --> 00:08:14,060
Don't you remember? We agreed on a contract.

72
00:08:14,060 --> 00:08:17,570
I want to keep doing it.

73
00:08:17,570 --> 00:08:20,480
This person, seriously...

74
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:26,190
Let's do it. Come out, I want to talk with you.

75
00:08:26,190 --> 00:08:30,610
With me? Talk about what?

76
00:08:30,610 --> 00:08:35,450
Well... everything. If it's about you.

77
00:08:44,470 --> 00:08:46,380
It's here.

78
00:08:48,650 --> 00:08:52,920
You said you'd take me somewhere amazing, so I had such high expectations.

79
00:08:52,920 --> 00:08:55,880
What is this?

80
00:08:55,880 --> 00:08:59,420
What's wrong with our neighborhood? It's pretty.

81
00:09:05,510 --> 00:09:08,030
It is pretty.

82
00:09:08,030 --> 00:09:09,830
I'll give you that.

83
00:09:17,350 --> 00:09:20,340
You said you wanted to know about me, right?

84
00:09:24,210 --> 00:09:28,380
I am... an orphan.

85
00:09:29,110 --> 00:09:31,920
I have only myself in this world.

86
00:09:37,770 --> 00:09:41,630
We were on our  way to visit the  arboretum.

87
00:09:41,630 --> 00:09:43,470
Let's lift her.

88
00:09:51,250 --> 00:09:53,320
Watch her head!

89
00:09:57,130 --> 00:09:58,630
There's a child here!

90
00:09:58,630 --> 00:10:05,400
Apparently my dad, who worked overtime a lot, fell asleep while driving.

91
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:07,370
Mom.

92
00:10:07,370 --> 00:10:11,490
I heard this all later from my uncle.

93
00:10:13,150 --> 00:10:17,080
Honestly, I don't remember those times at all.

94
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:23,490
According to my unni, it's because the shock was so big at the time.

95
00:10:23,490 --> 00:10:25,200
For me.

96
00:10:26,540 --> 00:10:32,280
For about a year, I didn't speak at all.

97
00:10:33,220 --> 00:10:38,010
I couldn't talk, I couldn't sleep at night.

98
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:42,480
Like now.

99
00:10:45,250 --> 00:10:48,790
How were you as a child?

100
00:10:50,950 --> 00:10:56,000
Since I told you about me, at least tell me one thing about you.

101
00:10:56,910 --> 00:10:58,530
Me?

102
00:10:59,680 --> 00:11:02,260
I was smart.

103
00:11:02,260 --> 00:11:06,130
I was the class president and played piano well.

104
00:11:06,130 --> 00:11:08,680
The best at soccer, too.

105
00:11:08,680 --> 00:11:12,040
I wasn't that bad-looking, either.

106
00:11:12,040 --> 00:11:16,310
I don't know if you noticed or not, but my family is super rich.

107
00:11:20,760 --> 00:11:23,170
Such a show-off.

108
00:11:25,990 --> 00:11:28,100
You don't have friends, right?

109
00:11:28,100 --> 00:11:29,930
Nope.

110
00:11:29,930 --> 00:11:31,540
Oh.

111
00:11:36,790 --> 00:11:38,740
Be careful.

112
00:11:54,830 --> 00:11:57,630
Can I kiss you?

113
00:12:10,700 --> 00:12:13,410
So, what I mean is...

114
00:12:15,270 --> 00:12:19,330
I'm so unbelievable, right? Even I think so.

115
00:12:19,330 --> 00:12:22,350
I mean, you know, I've had a lot of trauma in my life and

116
00:12:22,350 --> 00:12:26,750
I was wondering if maybe you and I are suffering from the same sort of pain.

117
00:12:26,750 --> 00:12:30,420
So I just asked so suddenly like that.

118
00:12:32,010 --> 00:12:34,720
I'm sorry for not coming up with a better excuse.

119
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:41,490
When I talk about my past, I become weak-hearted for some reason.

120
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:45,620
Let's go.

121
00:12:59,690 --> 00:13:03,250
♫ Can you hear it? ♫

122
00:13:03,250 --> 00:13:09,800
♫ When the wind blows through my heart ♫

123
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:13,450
♫ Can you feel it? ♫

124
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:19,900
♫ Our times spent together ♫

125
00:13:20,960 --> 00:13:28,370
♫ Today, you’re only looking at me ♫

126
00:13:30,010 --> 00:13:35,090
♫ Can’t you hear it? ♫

127
00:13:35,090 --> 00:13:39,900
♫ Can’t you see it? ♫

128
00:13:39,900 --> 00:13:45,100
♫ On that heart-fluttering day, ♫

129
00:13:45,100 --> 00:13:48,450
♫ on that beautiful day ♫

130
00:13:50,100 --> 00:13:55,600
♫ My heart trembled so much ♫

131
00:13:55,640 --> 00:14:00,020
♫ It keeps pounding ♫

132
00:14:00,100 --> 00:14:02,800
Did you sleep well? I"m on my way to work.

133
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:05,280
Good luck to us today, too!

134
00:14:06,280 --> 00:14:07,930
So cringe-worthy!

135
00:14:10,410 --> 00:14:15,270
♫ On that happy day, I’ll be loving you, ♫

136
00:14:15,270 --> 00:14:18,780
♫ to be loving you ♫

137
00:14:19,900 --> 00:14:23,250
♫ I’m gonna love with you ♫

138
00:14:24,530 --> 00:14:26,770
Hello!

139
00:14:56,290 --> 00:14:58,660
A pickpocket! He's a pickpocket!

140
00:14:59,430 --> 00:15:02,560
Sunbaenim, it's a pickpocket.

141
00:15:02,560 --> 00:15:05,400
Thief! Thief!

142
00:15:07,140 --> 00:15:09,360
Catch him!

143
00:15:19,730 --> 00:15:21,870
Hey!

144
00:15:21,870 --> 00:15:24,390
Let go.

145
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:36,800
Hit him! Hit him! Hit him!

146
00:15:46,330 --> 00:15:49,430
Police Station

147
00:15:58,060 --> 00:16:00,090
Are you alright?

148
00:16:00,090 --> 00:16:01,430
Yes.

149
00:16:01,430 --> 00:16:07,750
Sunbaenim, it looks as if you pooped in your pants.

150
00:16:08,850 --> 00:16:12,670
I know! I saw it too.

151
00:16:16,720 --> 00:16:19,350
Your face is a sight!

152
00:16:20,490 --> 00:16:22,360
I know.

153
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:28,360
I'm going to talk informally to you from now on.

154
00:16:28,360 --> 00:16:30,870
You've been doing that since before.

155
00:16:30,870 --> 00:16:33,250
The things you say...

156
00:16:34,230 --> 00:16:37,660
You have some time, right? Follow me.

157
00:16:41,970 --> 00:16:44,020
Wait here.

158
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:50,460
Hey. What happened to your face?

159
00:16:50,460 --> 00:16:52,560
Did you get into a fight?

160
00:16:53,620 --> 00:16:56,420
Something happened. I'll tell you later.

161
00:17:04,680 --> 00:17:06,470
You got punched by Sunbae Hwang?

162
00:17:06,470 --> 00:17:08,100
No.

163
00:17:08,100 --> 00:17:11,440
You can't get a day of the sleep you want.

164
00:17:15,630 --> 00:17:20,150
Ms. Hong Yi Yeong. Do you have time every Wednesday from six to seven p.m.?

165
00:17:20,150 --> 00:17:24,820
Sorry? Uh, yes, I do.

166
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:29,100
This is the address of the studio where I teach.

167
00:17:29,100 --> 00:17:33,410
I'll give you half off for lesson fees.

168
00:17:41,890 --> 00:17:46,180
It was your doing, right? Getting him to teach me.

169
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:50,100
- Do what? We just talked a little about life.
- Life?

170
00:17:50,120 --> 00:17:52,260
His wife who is in America is my junior.

171
00:17:52,300 --> 00:17:56,800
We were both oboists at the same university. I asked how she was doing.

172
00:17:56,800 --> 00:17:58,780
Sorry?

173
00:17:58,800 --> 00:18:02,400
Aren't you all going to the rehearsal? Let's not be late.

174
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:04,860
Yes, ma'am.

175
00:18:22,370 --> 00:18:26,820
Finally done with work. Make sure to eat dinner!

176
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:34,760
What are you doing tonight?

177
00:18:34,760 --> 00:18:38,060
Tonight? Oh, I'm not doing anything.

178
00:18:38,060 --> 00:18:41,090
Great. Pack your bag.

179
00:18:58,440 --> 00:19:01,580
Stop. Stop right there.

180
00:19:03,050 --> 00:19:05,650
Do you memorize the pieces?

181
00:19:05,700 --> 00:19:09,200
- Well, a bit.
- A bit?

182
00:19:12,170 --> 00:19:14,620
Spit your gum out.

183
00:19:17,820 --> 00:19:19,740
Spit it out.

184
00:19:25,120 --> 00:19:28,650
Gang Sin Yeong, your playing sucks.

185
00:19:28,650 --> 00:19:30,720
What did you say?

186
00:19:30,720 --> 00:19:32,730
Even though you know, you will continue to play.

187
00:19:32,730 --> 00:19:36,090
Because your family's money is as good as talent.

188
00:19:36,090 --> 00:19:39,580
However, you should know how things are. Your playing

189
00:19:39,580 --> 00:19:42,570
is like shit. And you're trash.

190
00:19:43,460 --> 00:19:47,400
Because of you, a talented poor person will be rejected.

191
00:19:47,400 --> 00:19:50,500
So what? Then what does that make you, who accepts my mom's money?

192
00:19:50,500 --> 00:19:54,210
You're the same trash. I want to stop for today.

193
00:20:10,720 --> 00:20:12,970
Bye.

194
00:20:15,170 --> 00:20:17,670
Go home safely.

195
00:20:17,670 --> 00:20:19,930
That rude brat.

196
00:20:25,250 --> 00:20:28,140
Not that you're much better.

197
00:20:28,140 --> 00:20:31,110
What are you trying to achieve by verbally fighting with them?

198
00:20:31,110 --> 00:20:35,080
Those kind of kids just need to pass the exam.

199
00:20:35,080 --> 00:20:37,630
You fight them because you don't know?

200
00:20:37,630 --> 00:20:39,760
I'm going.

201
00:20:40,470 --> 00:20:47,470
If you can't be a soloist, you have to be a teacher.

202
00:20:47,470 --> 00:20:49,260
Don't you think so?

203
00:20:49,260 --> 00:20:55,030
Keep being careful with her. She's the one the President specifically asked a favor for.

204
00:20:58,630 --> 00:21:00,790
Let's do well.

205
00:21:07,160 --> 00:21:08,970
They're all trash.

206
00:21:08,970 --> 00:21:10,510
I'm sorry?

207
00:21:11,830 --> 00:21:15,420
Sir, can you change the direction? Go to Sinyeong Music College.

208
00:21:29,060 --> 00:21:30,830
The music is pleasant.

209
00:21:30,830 --> 00:21:31,870
Welcome.

210
00:21:31,870 --> 00:21:33,730
Hello.

211
00:21:33,730 --> 00:21:35,760
Hello. Where is the professor?

212
00:21:35,760 --> 00:21:37,490
This way, please.

213
00:21:37,490 --> 00:21:40,910
All these welcoming people are coming all at once.

214
00:21:40,910 --> 00:21:44,710
You look good, Professor.  Were all your performances in Germany well received?

215
00:21:44,710 --> 00:21:48,150
I bribed all the journalists.

216
00:21:48,150 --> 00:21:50,280
It's the secret to living.

217
00:21:50,280 --> 00:21:52,980
I'll remember that.

218
00:21:53,960 --> 00:21:55,880
It's been a while, Professor.

219
00:21:55,880 --> 00:22:00,200
Aigoo, Yi Yeong, why is it so hard to see your face?

220
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:02,180
I heard you started playing in the Philharmonic?

221
00:22:02,180 --> 00:22:05,660
No, I got fired.

222
00:22:07,420 --> 00:22:08,790
Already?

223
00:22:08,790 --> 00:22:10,930
In one day.

224
00:22:10,930 --> 00:22:13,710
I'm going to do my audition again.

225
00:22:17,510 --> 00:22:19,060
Let's get a seat first.

226
00:22:19,060 --> 00:22:21,390
I'll bring you the meat quickly.

227
00:22:21,390 --> 00:22:22,600
Thank you.

228
00:22:22,600 --> 00:22:23,750
Thank you.

229
00:22:23,750 --> 00:22:24,490
Sit down.

230
00:22:24,490 --> 00:22:25,920
- Na Yeong?
- Yes?

231
00:22:25,920 --> 00:22:27,600
Take this.

232
00:22:28,470 --> 00:22:30,310
Hello.

233
00:23:12,170 --> 00:23:14,790
Beethoven Symphony op.7, 4th movement.

234
00:23:14,790 --> 00:23:17,540
Use a full bow when playing up bow.

235
00:23:17,540 --> 00:23:22,850
Keep your arm relaxed.  Flex your wrist when striking the bow.

236
00:23:36,860 --> 00:23:39,230
You have until 12.00 to finish the test.

237
00:23:39,230 --> 00:23:43,570
Those who are done can leave the test paper and quietly leave.

238
00:23:44,330 --> 00:23:49,890
And lastly, the guest pianist who captivated me, Mr. Jang Yun.

239
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:54,430
Where have I seen you?

240
00:23:55,230 --> 00:24:00,010
Take you concern off of me. I don't like people being interested in me.

241
00:24:06,900 --> 00:24:08,780
No way.

242
00:24:13,850 --> 00:24:18,010
No, professor. It's boring when I win three games.

243
00:24:18,940 --> 00:24:23,270
You get older too.  When your hands shake, you'll be out of business.

244
00:24:24,860 --> 00:24:29,590
You and I, let's do one more game, quietly. Let's go with baduk*.
(Korean board game, also called "Go")

245
00:24:29,590 --> 00:24:31,550
- Baduk sounds good.
- Good.

246
00:24:31,550 --> 00:24:34,300
What, you two know how to play baduk?

247
00:24:34,300 --> 00:24:37,110
Is there anything I can't do?

248
00:24:38,330 --> 00:24:39,510
- Na Yeong!
- Yes?

249
00:24:39,600 --> 00:24:42,400
- Fetch my baduk board from my office.
- Yes.

250
00:24:42,460 --> 00:24:43,680
No it's alright, I can go.

251
00:24:43,700 --> 00:24:46,400
Oh, alright.

252
00:24:48,210 --> 00:24:50,820
Let's see who wins.

253
00:24:56,440 --> 00:24:59,310
Did you sleep well?  I'm on my way to work. Good luck to us today too.

254
00:24:59,310 --> 00:25:02,020
Finally done with work. Make sure to eat dinner!

255
00:25:05,280 --> 00:25:09,040
I used all my resources to get your address.

256
00:25:09,040 --> 00:25:13,390
The information you put on your resumé, half of it is wrong.

257
00:25:14,130 --> 00:25:16,740
You are incredible.

258
00:25:16,740 --> 00:25:20,000
How did you get in the orchestra?

259
00:25:22,210 --> 00:25:25,220
You live near Hong Yi Yeong.

260
00:25:25,220 --> 00:25:29,020
Who would've known you live right below her.

261
00:25:31,590 --> 00:25:34,040
What do you want?

262
00:25:34,040 --> 00:25:39,690
I finally remembered where I've seen you.

263
00:25:39,690 --> 00:25:44,320
Your name isn't Jang Yun, is it?

264
00:25:45,070 --> 00:25:48,730
I couldn't handle my curiosity, so I came.

265
00:25:48,730 --> 00:25:54,220
What's your real name?

266
00:26:11,180 --> 00:26:13,780
Where is it?

267
00:26:22,330 --> 00:26:24,210
Is it here?

268
00:26:30,080 --> 00:26:32,290
Here it is!

269
00:26:43,040 --> 00:26:45,830
Are you crazy. What are you doing?

270
00:26:45,830 --> 00:26:47,270
When did it start?

271
00:26:47,270 --> 00:26:48,570
What do you mean?

272
00:26:48,570 --> 00:26:51,200
Oh you don't want to answer. Should I answer for you?

273
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:53,250
You're crazy.

274
00:26:53,250 --> 00:26:59,040
Something was sketchy about you since your piano performance. It was too similar to someone I know.

275
00:26:59,040 --> 00:27:02,890
Did you purposely run into Nam Ju Wan?

276
00:27:02,890 --> 00:27:05,000
So you can get into the orchestra through him?

277
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:06,210
Am I not allowed to do that?

278
00:27:06,210 --> 00:27:10,420
What is your real purpose?

279
00:27:10,420 --> 00:27:14,910
You're impersonating someone who died. Why have you shown up here?

280
00:27:22,320 --> 00:27:25,680
Asia Philharmonic Orchestra &
Kim Ian - Chopin Piano Concerto

281
00:27:29,450 --> 00:27:34,820
His name... Can I ask what your brother's name is?

282
00:27:36,480 --> 00:27:39,580
Kim Ian.

283
00:27:39,580 --> 00:27:41,680
Do you know him?

284
00:27:44,020 --> 00:27:47,470
What are you doing? Have you not found it yet?

285
00:27:56,990 --> 00:28:00,220
A dead person? Who?

286
00:28:08,120 --> 00:28:11,230
Asia Philharmonic Orchestra &
Kim Ian - Chopin Piano Concerto

287
00:28:12,610 --> 00:28:20,490
Conductor, do you know this person?

288
00:28:23,190 --> 00:28:25,930
Who?

289
00:28:25,930 --> 00:28:29,620
Then why are you so interested in me?

290
00:28:29,620 --> 00:28:33,220
Who are you worried about? What are you so scared of?

291
00:28:33,220 --> 00:28:35,710
Can I look into it?

292
00:28:35,710 --> 00:28:39,350
I can tell everyone that your name is fake.

293
00:28:39,350 --> 00:28:43,010
Tell them if you can. Can you do it?

294
00:28:47,200 --> 00:28:55,400
Conductor, don't you know this person, Kim Ian?

295
00:28:56,600 --> 00:29:00,100
Asia Philharmonic Orchestra &
Kim Ian - Chopin Piano Concerto

296
00:30:15,320 --> 00:30:21,950
♫ Even if it's the last time I hear your dazzling voice, it's all right ♫

297
00:30:22,800 --> 00:30:30,200
♫ Please let me hear your song so that I can live ♫

298
00:30:30,200 --> 00:30:34,150
I Wanna Hear Your Song Preview
♫ I've treasured it for a long time ♫

299
00:30:34,160 --> 00:30:35,200
Kim Ian?

300
00:30:35,200 --> 00:30:37,650
The one whose assistant you were?

301
00:30:37,650 --> 00:30:41,140
I was sleeping so I didn't even know my brother had died.

302
00:30:41,140 --> 00:30:43,100
You said his girlfriend is alive and well.

303
00:30:43,100 --> 00:30:46,240
That woman could be pretending not to know that she killed Ian.

304
00:30:46,240 --> 00:30:48,020
I saw you that night

305
00:30:48,020 --> 00:30:51,450
when you and Kim Ian left a year ago for the Asia Philharmonic.

306
00:30:51,450 --> 00:30:53,960
Hello?

307
00:30:53,960 --> 00:30:58,080
Hello? Who are you?

308
00:30:59,920 --> 00:31:02,430
It's been a long time.

309
00:31:03,420 --> 00:31:07,320
♫ Even if I’m a flower without a scent ♫
